2 Sec. 2. Section 79-2,136, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
3 amended to read:
4 79-2,136 (1) Each school board shall allow the part-time enrollment
5 of students, for all courses selected by the students, who are residents
6 of, or admitted to, the school district pursuant to subsection
7 subsections (1), and (2), or (11) of section 79-215 and who are also
8 enrolled in a private, denominational, or parochial school or in a school
9 which elects pursuant to section 79-1601 not to meet accreditation or
10 approval requirements and shall establish policies and procedures for
11 such part-time enrollment. Such policies and procedures may include
12 provisions permitting the part-time enrollment of such students who are
13 not residents of, or admitted to, such school districts to the extent
14 permitted pursuant to section 79-215 and may require part-time students
15 to follow school policies that apply to other students at any time the
16 part-time student is present on school grounds or at a school-sponsored
17 activity or athletic event. Part-time enrollment shall not entitle a
18 student to transportation or transportation reimbursements pursuant to
19 section 79-611.
20 (2) Each school board shall establish policies and procedures to
21 allow any student who is a resident of, or admitted to, the school
22 district pursuant to subsection (1), or (2), or (11) of section 79-215
23 and who is enrolled in a school which elects pursuant to section 79-1601
24 not to meet accreditation or approval requirements to participate in any
25 extracurricular activities as defined in section 79-2,126, including, but
26 not limited to, interschool competitions, to the same extent and subject
27 to the same requirements, conditions, and procedures as a student
28 enrolled in a public school governed by such board, except that any
29 school which elects pursuant to section 79-1601 not to meet accreditation
30 or approval requirements shall set the standards for satisfactory
31 academic performance for a student from the school to participate in
-7-

