1 extracurricular activities pursuant to this subsection and shall provide
2 assurances of compliance with such academic standards.
3 (3) School board policies and procedures adopted pursuant to
4 subsection (2) of this section (a) shall require any student desiring to
5 participate participating in extracurricular activities pursuant to such
6 subsection to be enrolled in no more and no less than five credit hours
7 offered by the school district in any semester in order to participate,
8 but may not prohibit a student from enrolling in more than five credit
9 hours, (b) shall not allow any preference in the selection of a student
10 for participation in an extracurricular activity based on such student's
11 status as a full-time student in the school district, and (c) may require
12 any student participating in extracurricular activities pursuant to such
13 subsection to follow school policies that apply to other students when
14 present on school grounds or at a school-sponsored activity or athletic
15 event. Participation in extracurricular activities pursuant to subsection
16 (2) of this section shall not entitle a student to transportation, except
17 to and from practices and events to the same extent as public school
18 students participating in such activities, or transportation
19 reimbursement pursuant to section 79-611.
20 (4) Nothing in this section shall be construed to exempt any student
21 from the compulsory attendance provisions of section sections 79-201 or
22 any statutes relating to habitual truancy to 79-210.
